    Formula And.dual()
    Returns the dual of this formula (And)
    In general, the dual of And is represented by the following transformation:
    (f1 && f2) -> (!f1 || !f2)
    Formula BinaryFormula.dual()
    Returns the dual of this binary formula.
    Formula ConstantFormula.dual()
    Returns the dual of this constant formula.
    Formula False.dual()
    Returns the dual of this formula (False)
    In general, the dual of false is represented by the following transformation:
    !false -> true
    abstract Formula Formula.dual()  
    Formula Next.dual()
    Returns the dual of this formula (Next)
    In general, the dual of next is represented by the following transformation:
    !Xf -> X!f
    Formula Not.dual()
    Returns the dual of this formula (Not)
    In general, the dual of not is the dual of it's subformula
    Formula Or.dual()
    Returns the dual of this formula (Or)
    In general, the dual of Or is represented by the following transformation:
    (f1 || f2) -> (!f1 && !f2)
    Formula True.dual()
    Returns the dual of this formula (True)
    In general, the dual of true is represented by the following transformation:
    !true -> false
    Formula UnaryFormula.dual()  
    Formula Until.dual()
    Returns the dual of this formula (Until)
    In general, the dual of until is represented by the following transformation:
    !(f1 U f2) -> ((f1 && !f2) W (!f1 && !f2))
    Formula WeakUntil.dual()
    Returns the dual of this formula (Weak Until)
    In general, the dual of weak until is represented by the following transformation:
    !(f1 W f2) -> ((f1 && !f2) U (!f1 && !f2))

    Methods in v that return Formula 
    Modifier and Type Method Description
    Formula FormulaVisitor.visit​(BinaryFormula binaryFormula)
    Visits a Binary LTL formula
    Firstly, the left and right subformulas are visited and then on the traversal back up a new Formula is generated consisting of the type of Binary formula this formula is and it's left and right subformulas
    Formula FormulaVisitor.visit​(ConstantFormula constantFormula)
    Visits a constant LTL formula
    Generally, a constant is a leaf in an expression tree and this signifies the end of a particular branch of the formula.
    Formula FormulaVisitor.visit​(Formula formula)
    Visits a generic LTL formula
    Formula FormulaVisitor.visit​(UnaryFormula unaryFormula)
    Visits a unary LTL formula
    Firstly, it is determined whether the unary formula is of type Not and if so, distributes the Not into the subformula by applying the correct dual transformation.
